<title>USA: BEFORE THE BELL-Philip Morris up, Adobe off.</title>
<headline>BEFORE THE BELL-Philip Morris up, Adobe off.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-06-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Philip Morris Cos Inc shares climbed almost two points preceding Thursday's U.S. market open on expectations tobacco settlement talks could yield an agreement as early as today, traders said.</p>
<p>Preceding the opening bell, Philip Morris shares traded at 47-3/8, up from 45-1/2 at Wednesday's New York Stock Exchange close, traders said.</p>
<p>RJR Nabisco Holdings Corp shares were not active in early third market trade, but were quoted at 35 bid, 36 ask, above last night's NYSE's close of 34-1/4, traders said.</p>
